column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Mostly Cloudy  No Precipitation  Light Wind
column13: Returned to section tested two weeks prior. Ice at this section had rotted out presumably due to higher temperatures around -15 degrees in the past week. Large open holes in ice with flow and bridged ice present at this section approximately 20m upstream of the bridge. Adjacent in the area too thin for safe measurement. Open leads with flow exist directly below the bridge with overflow in the vicinity. Ice at measurement section 5-10m downstream of the bridge were near minimum for safe measurement.
column14: Section by section ice measurement with StreamPro 5-10m downstream of the HWY4/Cameron Ramparts bridge. Measurement seems to be of good quality with low uncertainty and symmetrical profile with flow concentrated in the centre of channel. Some difficulty capturing verticals particularly near left bank assumed to be due to low effective depth changing cell size did not sufficiently improve the number of good depth cells 2m from IP but did allow for measurement at tag mark 3m and from 8-10m where some difficulty was initially experienced. Surging water in holes and occasional release of air bubbles. This measurement section has been considered inferior in the past due to uneven flow distribution and higher flow angles than section 50m or so downstream of the gauge. Ice conditions at that section were observed two weeks ago to be unsafe for access using inflatable Zodiac boat. Gauge section was not visited today due to time constraints but conditions not expected to have changed significantly since last visit. Thus the chosen measurement section was the only safe one available. Final corrected MGH will be calculated after next DWL. Will attempt to prioritize visit within the next month.
